product_name: Jouer Cosmetics Blush Bouquet Dual Blush Palette
user_specs: ['Age 45-54', 'Eye Color Green', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Light', 'Skin Type Dry']
review_title: Is there something higher than Holy Grail?
review_content:
This is my can't live without it blush. I am blush obsessed and own an embarrassing amount. Yet most sit untouched because I can't stop using this one Jouer duo. It is perfect. The lighter side is the most beautiful matte cool toned pale pink. I don't know if it will work for skin tones darker than medium, but if you are in the fair to medium range I can not stress enough how gorgeous this shade is on the skin...like the natural kind of flush you would get if a naked Chris Hemsworth was standing in front of you with open arms and a wicked smile. The deeper shade is a gorgeous matte cool tone berry and it is quite pigmented and can built up for a variety of skin tones. This one looks beautiful on the skin as well. They are look great mixed, but I usually wear one on the cheekbones and the other on my apples for a pop of color. I saw that some other people had some issues with their duos cracking. I've had this one for over a year and I literally don't leave home without it and it's held up fine. And I'm not particularly careful with it either. My packaging has not peeled like others have as well. Besides the dent I've put in it, it looks just as good as when I got it. My sister spied it in my tote bag o' makeup not too long ago and oohed and ahhed over it when she was putting it on. Since I often pass makeup on when I'm not using it or don't love it she asked if it was something I was attached to and I had to fight the sudden urge to scratch her eyes out. I ended up screaming NO, snatched it out of her greedy hands, and cradled it to my breasts while she looked at me like I was crazy. And that's how much I love this Jouer blush duo. Hard and irrationally and I can't live without it.

product_name: Jouer Cosmetics Blush Bouquet Dual Blush Palette
user_specs: ['Eye Color Blue', 'Hair color Auburn', 'Skin Tone Porcelain', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_title: Great Blush But Breaks after Light Use
review_content:
I started out absolutely loving this blush duo for over a year. It's got an awesome formula that blends effortlessly but never looks like too much. I'm extremely pale and freckled, and when I mix the two shades it's my perfect nude blush. Unfortunately, the blush just breaks too easily. After everyday use for almost a year, my first Adore duo started cracking (just on the Adore side- left side). It fell apart when I was traveling one day (I only ever keep it in my backpack so no one is throwing it around in the hold on planes). Half of it dropped when I opened it so I ordered a new one. Within 2 months of having the new one, Adore cracked AGAIN. I re-pressed it, and it held up for a week, but as soon as I traveled with it it started to crumble. I am so bummed because this is my favorite nude blush ever, but I can't keep shelling out $30 for it to have it break within a few weeks. Maybe if you never travel or take it with you on nights out, it would hold up fine, but that's just not practical for my lifestyle. Wouldn't recommend if you're a person on the go. I'll be finding an alternative to replace it.

review_title: Rose Gold shade is NOT rosy.
review_content:
I picked this up at my local store yesterday, and was really excited to use it this morning! Unfortunately, this product was a definite fail, for me. In the pan, swatched on the back of my hand and arm, this had a rosy hue (as suggested in the name Rose Gold). I fully am aware that the description mentions a peachy glow, however...on my face today, it pulled some serious orange. Kind of bizarre. Not remotely rosy OR peachy, but orange. It is very pigmented, which would be WONDERFUL if the color is right for you! It was a big drawback in my situation, because I generally “over do” my blush a bit, so I can then blend/buff it down with translucent loose powder. This blush really did not want to blend out though.

product_name: Jouer Cosmetics Blush Bouquet Dual Blush Palette
user_specs: ['Age 25-34', 'Eye Color Hazel', 'Hair color Auburn', 'Skin Tone Tan', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content:
I am upset! I wanted this blush for so long because of the very bright warm pink color, only to find out it is no where near as bright in person. What is the difference between this and a 5$ walmart blush? The color is much lighter/less bright in person, and not only that, but to get any decent color pay off on my medium skin tone I have to apply quite a bit. The lighter color doesn't show up AT ALL. What is it? a very useless highlighter? It takes a while for this to show up on me and aside from the gorgeous packaging it's useless for me. I am returning in the hopes of trying maybe the Laura Mercier blush... This might work if you are like German or Swedish super pale but not if you have any darker ethnicity whatsoever.

review_title: Patchy and does not blend out well.
review_content:
Coquette is more muted and neutral in real life than the photo on here would suggest. The berry shade almost pulls a bit warm on my light cool/neutral olive complexion. The berry blush is what I describe as aggressively pigmented. No matter how little I pick up or which brush I use, I always end up with too much on my cheek and... it stays patchy and doesn't blend out. I have to use my MAC Skinfinish Natural powder to blend it out. The light pink is indeed cool but more muted in person and really doesn't doesn't do much of anything. I expected to love this blush duo. But every time I use it, which is daily, it's too much work and often looks very matte and blotchy. Wished I kept the box, I would have returned it.
